NC_000962.3	Mycobrowser_v4	CDS	3267737	3272203	.	+	0	Name=ppsE;Function=Involved in phenolpthiocerol and phthiocerol dimycocerosate (dim) biosynthesis: extension with malony CoA (partial reduction, decarboxylation).;Product=Phenolpthiocerol synthesis type-I polyketide synthase PpsE;Comments=Rv2935, (MTCY19H9.03), len: 1488 aa. PpsE, type-I polyketide synthase (see citations below). Contains PS00606 Beta-ketoacyl synthases active site. Note that Rv2935|ppsE belongs to the transcriptional unit Rv2930|fadD26-Rv2939|papA5 (proven experimentally). TesA|Rv2928 interacts with PpsE|Rv2935, by bacterial two-hybrid and GST-pulldown assays (See Rao and Ranganathan, 2004).;UniProt_AC=P9WQE1;Is_Pseudogene=No;Functional_Category=lipid metabolism;Protein Data Bank=;PFAM=P96204;UniProt=P9WQE1;Gene Ontology=GO:0009058,GO:0048037,GO:0016740,GO:0000036;Enzyme Classification=;Drug Resistance Mutations=;InterPro=;UniProtKB/TrEMBL=;SWISS-MODEL=P9WQE1;Parent=transcript:Rv2935_t1;ID=cds:Rv2935_c1
