NC_000962.3	Mycobrowser_v4	CDS	3230738	3231076	.	-	0	Name=glnB;Function=In nitrogen-limiting conditions, when the ratio of GLN to 2-ketoglutarate decreases, P-II is uridylylated to P-II-UMP by GLND|Rv2918c. P-II-UMP allows the deadenylylation of glutamine synthetase (gs), thus activating the enzyme. Converserly, in nitrogen excess P-II is deuridylated and promotes the adenylation of gs. P-II indirectly controls the transcription of the gs gene (GLNA: four copies in the genome). P-II prevents NR-II catalyzed conversion of NR-I to NR-I-phosphate, the transcriptional activator of GLNA. When P-II is uridylylated to P-II-UMP, these events are reversed.;Product=Probable nitrogen regulatory protein P-II GlnB;Comments=Rv2919c, (MTCY338.08c), len: 112 aa. Probable glnB, nitrogen regulatory protein, highly similar to others e.g. Q9X705|GLNB PII protein from Corynebacterium glutamicum (Brevibacterium flavum) (112 aa), FASTA scores: opt: 531, E(): 4.5e-30, (68.75% identity in 112 aa overlap);UniProt_AC=P9WN31;Is_Pseudogene=No;Functional_Category=regulatory proteins;Protein Data Bank=3BZQ,3LF0;PFAM=P64249;UniProt=P9WN31;Gene Ontology=GO:0000166,GO:0006808,GO:0045449,GO:0006350,GO:0030234;Enzyme Classification=;Drug Resistance Mutations=;InterPro=;UniProtKB/TrEMBL=;SWISS-MODEL=P9WN31;Parent=transcript:Rv2919c_t1;ID=cds:Rv2919c_c1
